data.text:
The Mid South Wrestling Television Review with Mike Mills & The Great Brian Last is back this week, looking at Mid South television from November 12, 1983, featuring:

Will Hacksaw Butch Reed be fined for what he did to King Cobra?

Hacksaw Butch Reed and Jim Neidhart are interviewed by Jim Ross with a wet dog?

Nikolai Volkoff takes on Krusher Darsow.

The Road Warriors (The National Tag Champs) return to Mid-South.

Magnum T.A. and Mr. Wrestling II sit down with Reiser Bowden for an important announcement on their partnership.

All of that and more on another action packed episode of the Mid-South Television Review podcast!

Produced by Jayce Naccarato

The Mid South Wrestling Television Review is a production of the Arcadian Vanguard Podcast Network
